{
  "corpus_id": "docs.docs_maintenance_corpus.beta",
  "schema_version": 1,
  "description": "Conformance drill corpus for the M3 docs preview / maintenance integrity beta lane. Every drill reuses the canonical docs-maintenance records and validation owned by aureline-docs::maintenance (DocsPreviewHeader, DocsSuggestionCard, DocsExampleFindingRow, DocsMaintenanceRow, DocsMaintenanceContract, DocsMaintenanceReviewPacket); the runner never re-implements the ruleset. Every positive drill MUST validate cleanly (zero findings), match every pinned expected_* token, and carry no raw URL or raw-body export. Every negative drill MUST FAIL validation with at least one finding whose check_id contains expected_violation_check_id (review-packet drift is checked against the seeded contract). The corpus proves the M3 docs-maintenance exit-gate: preview/rendering stays safe and labeled with a CommonMark baseline, suggestions stay evidence-backed diffs that are never silently applied, stale-example and broken-link findings stay specific and attributable, and README/changelog maintenance preserves branch/channel/audience truth across desktop, CLI, and exported review packets. Hidden renderer extensions, silent suggestion application, unscoped README/changelog updates, dropped suppression attribution, and wrong-channel maintenance are pinned as FAILING drills rather than tolerated.",
